Overview
This documents the full build of a home red team lab from scratch in a single session. The
lab consists of a bare-metal Kali Linux attack machine, a bare-metal Windows 10 Pro target
machine, and an isolated lab network using a dedicated router and managed switch — all
physically segmented from the home network.
By end of session: attack machine successfully enumerated the target and established an
authenticated RDP session.

