Key Lessons Learned
Legacy vs UEFI matters. The E6230 runs Legacy BIOS, requiring MBR partition scheme on
the USB. The MSI runs UEFI but was switched to Legacy mode to resolve Secure Boot MOK
NVRAM issues with Kali.
DNS can break silently. NetworkManager overwrites /etc/resolv.conf on network changes.
Locking it with chattr +i prevents silent breakage during apt operations.
RDP is loud. Connecting via standard RDP kicks the active console session off the target —
an obvious indicator. Shadow sessions ( /shadow:1 /noconsentprompt ) are required for
stealth in real engagements.
Network isolation is non-negotiable. An unpatched Windows machine should never sit on
the same network as personal devices. The MT3000 provides the boundary that makes safe
lab operation possible.

